Index emission policy:
  fk_indexable(kind):   kind ∈ { Int, Record(_) }
  for each fk-indexable field on a table:
    emit DEFINE INDEX idx_<Table>_<col> ON TABLE <Table> FIELDS <col>;
    immediately after the field line
  index is NON-UNIQUE by default:
    `has_one` 1:1 relations would warrant UNIQUE but that signal is
    not in the current ruff vocabulary; non-unique is safe.

Index naming:
  idx_<Table>_<col>  e.g. idx_TimeEntry_work_package_id
  - Table stays PascalCase (matches SurrealDB DEFINE TABLE name)
  - col stays snake_case (matches the field name)
  - mixed casing is fine in SurrealDB identifiers; the consistent
    pattern (table identifier as emitted, field identifier as emitted)
    keeps the index name a deterministic function of the inputs.

